Make pest_consume's generated parser reproducible.

The `#[pest_consume::parser]` macro builds the `AliasedRule` enum, its
dispatch/shortcut match arms, and the synthesized alias methods by iterating a
`std::collections::HashMap`. HashMap iteration order is randomized per process,
so the generated code (and therefore the crate's metadata SVH) comes out
differently on every compile. That non-determinism propagates through every
crate that links the `dhall` parser (dhall -> serde_dhall -> devenv-core -> ...)
and breaks binary-cache reuse: a build that mixes a cached crate with a freshly
built dependent hits rustc E0463 "can't find crate" on an SVH mismatch.

Sort each generated collection so the macro output is deterministic.

Upstream: https://github.com/Nadrieril/pest_consume

